Ghost could barely keep up as he and his master trailed the creatures wake. Its wings spread wide for added speed hung like a darker cloud over its form. Occasionally the moonlight would glint off the tallons which graced its hands. <br>
A soft snarl reached the ears of the rider as the creature came to a halt, it crouched low as though scenting a track. Its eyes glinted eiriely as it turned briefly to face him. He could make out the fangs, so close was he, the sight making his heart race in both fear and awe. As it rose he noted the supple form. Female by all accounts. Kneeing Ghost the rider moved forward as the creature sprinted once more into a run. Yes, it was definatly tracking something. The question was what?<br>
In the distance the rider could make out the faint glow of a dying fire and knew instinctively that the person or persons about the fire where the creatures prey. He spurred the horse on to circle the encampment. To come from the opposite side of the creature. From the darkness he could make out the silver hair of the occupant of the camp. A young man lay stretched out upon his bedroll lost to sleep, but not for long as suddenly its battlecry filled the air. <br>
Before the young man could even rise he found himself held fast to the ground, frightened emerald eyes met the hatred burried deep in the darker emerald eyes the creature. It hissed at him as it raised a taloned hand over his head. <br>
&quot;Stop!&quot; Nos cried out as he recognized the man, boy really. Not more than twenty perhaps. He lept from the back of his horse and charged into the camp. No thought of his own welfare only that of saving his child and his bondmate. &quot;Kat, wait.. please Ma' Vie.. dont.. &quot; his voice softened as he drew nearer, attempting to calm the rage and hatred in the creatures eyes as it swung its head to look upon the intruder, it hissed softly, &quot;How dare you, mortal, interfer in the fathers work?&quot; It rose then, an unuttered spell holding the boy fast as it stepped over him and approached the prophet. &quot;Do you know the price for interfering in the Fathers Wrath?&quot; It growled at him as its body coiled, preparing to strike. &quot;Kat, you cant, not our son.. think.. dont let him do this to you, to us.... &quot; Nos found his words cut short as he was suddenly, and roughly flung to the ground. The speed at which it had struck him had left him no time to prepare. He found himself now laying beside his son, equally paralyzed. <br>
It chuckled softly as it crouched between the two men, &quot;night and day.. &quot; it whispered softly as it took its leasuire at studying the contrasting difference between the two men,&quot; The father will be pleased at this nights offering. Kelebrindor!&quot; its gaze then fell exclusively on the boy, &quot;Your existance is an abomination in the eyes of the Father, for this you will meet your end. Nospiratus!&quot; It turned then to look upon the father, &quot;You have interefered for the last time in the work of the Father, You too shall pay the ultimate price.&quot;<br>
Almost gently a taloned hand come to rest against each exposed neck, for a brief moment cupping the curve, then with a singlure vicious swipe the skin was parted and the jugular severed on both. Their blood mingled and drenched the earth. &quot;Return to the abyss of hatred, to feed the fires..&quot; It growled, its words the last either would ever hear, as their lifes blood stained the ground. <br>
As the life flickered then seeped from two pair of eyes the creature sat back upon its heels, its head lowering as a sudden overwhelming pain engulfed it. An inner pain never felt before. A howl of rage broke from it.. &quot;No!&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;NO!&quot; Kat woke with a start, her heart pounding with fear. Her hands moved frantically to craddle the still growing child within her. &quot;No.. &quot; she whispered softly. &quot;What is it Ma' Vie,&quot; Nos asked softly as his hands reached to pull her down beside him. His arms coming about her to craddle her against him. &quot;A dream.. just a bad dream.. &quot; she whispered softly, trying to convince herself. &quot;Aye Ma' Vie.. just a bad dream, rest now. Close your eyes. Nothing will harm you.&quot; Nos' words soothed her back to sleep. Yet even as she slept he remained vigilant. A dream he had said, but was it really. Or was it a omen of what was to come should their path sway?<br>
